FBIS4-42440 "drweu107_j_94008" FBIS-WEU-94-107 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Scalfaro: Italy `Fundamentally Stable' Scalfaro: Italy `Fundamentally Stable' LD0206125894 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1235 GMT 2 Jun 94 LD0206125894 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] After the recent international polemics and just after having held talks with U.S. President Bill Clinton, the president [Scalfaro] has once again stressed that Italy "is fundamentally stable and reliable on the international scene," in spite of the changes which are taking place in our country and the "presence of new political groupings." Scalfaro was addressing 125 diplomats to celebrate Republic Day. He repeated that Italy "has the right to be respected by all those who think that substance is more important than form; it must be more important than form."
